        <!-- Q1 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    <m>\lim\limits_{(x,y)\to (0,0)}\frac{xy}{2-\sqrt{xy+4}}</m>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    先将分母有理化</p>
                    <p>
                        <m>\begin{aligned}
                        原式 &amp; =\lim\limits_{(x,y)\to (0,0)}\frac{xy(2+\sqrt{xy+4})}{4-(xy+4)}\\
                        &amp; =\underset{(x,y)\to (0,0)}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{xy(2+\sqrt{xy+4}}{-xy}\\
                        &amp; =-4
                        \end{aligned}</m> 
                </p>
            </answer>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    先恒等变形，然后利用等价无穷小代换</p>
                    <p> <m>\begin{aligned}
                    原式 &amp; =\underset{(x,y)\to (0,0)}{\mathop{\lim }}\ \frac{xy}{2-2\sqrt{\frac{xy}{4}+1}}\\
                    &amp; =\underset{(x,y)\to (0,0)}{\mathop{\lim }}\ \frac{xy}{2\left( 1-\sqrt{\frac{xy}{4}+1} \right)}\\
                    &amp; =\underset{xy\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{xy}{2\left( \frac{-xy}{4}\cdot \frac{1}{2} \right)}\\
                    &amp; =-4
                    \end{aligned}</m>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q2 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    <m>\lim\limits_{(x, y) \rightarrow(0,0)} \frac{1-\cos \sqrt{x y}}{\sqrt{2-\mathrm{e}^{x y}}-1}</m>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <m>\begin{array}{l}
                        =\lim\limits_{(x, y) \rightarrow(0,0)} \frac{1-\cos \sqrt{x y}}{\sqrt{1+\left(1-\mathrm{e}^{x y}\right)}-1} \\
                        =\lim\limits_{(x, y) \rightarrow(0,0)} \frac{\frac{(\sqrt{x y})^{2}}{2}}{\frac{1-\mathrm{e}^{x y}}{2}} \\
                        =-1 
                        \end{array}</m>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q3 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    证明：<m>f(x,y)=\frac{x{{y}^{2}}}{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{4}}}</m>在原点<m>(0,0)</m>的极限不存在
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    【分析】观察分子、分母中变量 <m>x,y</m> 的各次幂的特点，可考虑选择路径 <m>x=k{{y}^{2}}</m>，以便使分子分母中的部分零因子可以约去.</p>

                    <p> 解：因为
                        
                        <me>\begin{aligned}
                        \underset{\begin{matrix}
                           y\to 0  \\
                           x\to k{{y}^{2}}  \\
                        \end{matrix}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,f(x,y) &amp; =\underset{\begin{matrix}
                           y\to 0  \\
                           x=k{{y}^{2}}  \\
                        \end{matrix}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{x{{y}^{2}}}{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{4}}}\\
                         &amp; =\underset{y\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{k{{y}^{4}}}{{{k}^{2}}{{y}^{4}}+{{y}^{4}}}\\
                         &amp; =\frac{k}{{{k}^{2}}+1}
                        \end{aligned}</me></p>

                        <p>故<m>\lim\limits_{(x,y)\to (0,0)}f(x,y)</m>不存在。
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q4 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设<m>f(x,y)=\left\{ \begin{array}{*{35}{l}}
                        \frac{{{x}^{2}}-{{y}^{2}}}{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}},  &amp;  {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}\ne 0  \\
                        0,  &amp;  {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}=0  \\
                     \end{array} \right.</m>，讨论<m>f(x,y)</m>的连续性
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    【分析】二元函数<m>f(x,y)</m>在<m>({{x}_{0}},{{y}_{0}})</m>点连续的充要条件是<m>\lim\limits_{(x,y)\to \left( {{x}_{0}},{{y}_{0}} \right)}f(x,y)=f\left( {{x}_{0}},{{y}_{0}} \right)</m></p>
                        
                    <p>本题中的函数<m>f(x,y)</m>是一个分段函数，因<m>\frac{{{x}^{2}}-{{y}^{2}}}{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}}</m>是二元初等函数，在其定义域<m>{{\mathbf{R}}^{2}}-|(0,0)|</m>内每一点处是连续的，故只需考虑<m>f(x,y)</m>在<m>(0,0)</m>处的连续性。</p>
                    
                    <p> 解：考虑极限<m>\lim\limits_{(x,y)\to (0,0)}\frac{{{x}^{2}}-{{y}^{2}}}{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}}</m>，当<m>(x,y)</m>沿直线<m>y=kx</m>趋于<m>(0,0)</m>时</p>
                    <p><me>\begin{aligned}
                         &amp; \underset{\begin{matrix}
                           (x,y)\to (0,0)  \\
                           y=kx  \\
                        \end{matrix}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{x}^{2}}-{{y}^{2}}}{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}}\\= &amp; \underset{x\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{x}^{2}}-{{(kx)}^{2}}}{{{x}^{2}}+{{(kx)}^{2}}}\\
                        = &amp; \frac{1-{{k}^{2}}}{1+{{k}^{2}}}
                        \end{aligned}</me></p>
                        <p>
                        这是一个与<m>k</m>有关的数值，从而当<m>(x,y)</m>沿不同路径趋于<m>(0,0)</m>时， <m>\frac{{{x}^{2}}-{{y}^{2}}}{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}}</m>趋于不同的极限，故极限<m>\lim\limits_{(x,y)\to (0,0)}\frac{{{x}^{2}}-{{y}^{2}}}{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}}</m>不存在，<m>\lim\limits_{(x,y)\to \left( {{x}_{0}},{{y}_{0}} \right)}f(x,y)</m>也不存在，<m>f(x,y)</m>在<m>(0,0)</m>点不连续。</p>
                        <p>
                        另外，当<m>(x,y)\ne (0,0)</m>时，<m>f(x,y)=\frac{{{x}^{2}}-{{y}^{2}}}{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}}</m>是二元初等函数，故它在<m>{{\mathbf{R}}^{2}}-|(0,0)|</m>内处处连续。
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q5 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设<m>z=x\sin (xy)+{{\text{e}}^{x+2y}}</m>，求<m>\frac{\partial z}{\partial x}</m>，<m>\frac{\partial z}{\partial y}</m>，<m>\frac{\partial z}{\partial x}\left| _{\begin{smallmatrix} 
                        x=1 \\ 
                        y=0 
                       \end{smallmatrix}} \right.</m>
                </p>
                    
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <m>\begin{aligned}
                        \frac{\partial z}{\partial x} &amp; =\sin (xy)+x\cos (xy)\cdot y+{{\text{e}}^{x+2y}}\cdot 1 \\ 
                       &amp;  =\sin (xy)+xy\cos (xy)+{{\text{e}}^{x+2y}} \\ 
                       \frac{\partial z}{\partial y} &amp; =x\cos (xy)\cdot x+{{\text{e}}^{x+2y}}\cdot 2 \\ 
                       &amp;  ={{x}^{2}}\cos (xy)+2{{\text{e}}^{x+2y}} \\ 
                       {{\left. \frac{\partial z}{\partial x} \right|}_{\begin{smallmatrix} 
                      x=1 \\ 
                      y=0 
                     \end{smallmatrix}}} &amp; =\text{e} \\ 
                     \end{aligned}</m> 
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q6 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设<m>f(x,y)=\frac{\sin xy\cos \sqrt{y+2}-(y-1)\cos x}{1+\sin x+\sin (y-1)}</m>，则<m>{{f}_{y}}(0,1)=</m>____
                </p>
            </statement>
            <hint>
                <p>
                    利用偏导数的定义来解
                </p>
            </hint>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <m>\begin{aligned}
                        {{f}_{y}}(0,1) &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{f(0,1+\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y)-f(0,1)}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y}\\
                         &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{-\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y}{(1+\sin \text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y)\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y}\\
                         &amp; =-1
                        \end{aligned}</m> 
                </p>
            </answer>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    <m>f(0,y)=\frac{1-y}{1+\sin (y-1)}</m>，故
                    <m>\begin{aligned}
                    {{f}_{y}}(0,y) &amp; =\frac{d}{dy}\left[ \frac{1-y}{1+\sin (y-1)} \right]\\
                    &amp; =\frac{-[1+\sin (y-1)]-(1-y)\cos (y-1)}{{{[1+\sin (y-1)]}^{2}}}
                    \end{aligned}</m></p>
                    <p>从而 <m>{{f}_{y}}(0,1)=-1</m>
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q7 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    求设<m>f(x,y)={{\text{e}}^{\sqrt{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{4}}}}}</m>，则函数在原点偏导数存在的情况是
                </p>
            </statement>
            <choices>
                <choice>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            <m>{{f}_{x}}(0,0)</m>，<m>{{f}_{y}}(0,0)</m>均存在
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                </choice>
                
                <choice >
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            <m>{{f}_{x}}(0,0)</m>存在，<m>{{f}_{y}}(0,0)</m>不存在
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                </choice>

                <choice correct="yes">
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            <m>{{f}_{x}}(0,0)</m>不存在，<m>{{f}_{y}}(0,0)</m>存在
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                </choice>

                <choice>
                    <statement>
                        <p>
                            <m>{{f}_{x}}(0,0)</m>，<m>{{f}_{y}}(0,0)</m>都不存在
                        </p>
                    </statement>
                </choice>
            
            </choices>
            
			<answer>
                	<p>
                        解：
                        <me>\begin{aligned}
                        {{f}_{x}}(0,0) &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{f(0+\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x,0)-f(0,0)}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x}\\
                         &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{\text{e}}^{\sqrt{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }{{x}^{2}}+{{0}^{4}}}}}-1}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x}\\
                         &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{\text{e}}^{|\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x|}}-1}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x}
                        \end{aligned}</me> </p>
                        <p>因为<m>\begin{aligned}
                        \underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x\to {{0}^{+}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{\text{e}}^{|\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x|}}-1}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x} &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x\to {{0}^{+}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{\text{e}}^{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x}}-1}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x}\\
                         &amp; =1,\\
                        \underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x\to {{0}^{-}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{\text{e}}^{|\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x|}}-1}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x} &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x\to {{0}^{-}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{\text{e}}^{-\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x}}-1}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x}\\
                         &amp; =-1
                        \end{aligned}</m> </p>
                        <p>故<m>\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x\to {{0}^{+}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{e}^{|\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x|}}-1}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x}\ne \underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x\to {{0}^{-}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{e}^{|\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x|}}-1}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }x}</m>，</p>
                        <p>所以<m>{{f}_{x}}(0,0)</m>不存在</p>
                        <p><m>\begin{aligned}
                        {{f}_{y}}(0,0) &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{f(0,0+\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y)-f(0,0)}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y}\\
                         &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{\text{e}}^{\sqrt{{{0}^{2}}+\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }{{y}^{4}}}}}-1}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y}\\
                         &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{{{\text{e}}^{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }{{y}^{2}}}}-1}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y}\\
                         &amp; =\underset{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }{{y}^{2}}}{\text{ }\!\!\Delta\!\!\text{ }y}=0
                        \end{aligned}</m></p>
                        <p>所以 <m>{{f}_{y}}(0,0)=0</m>存在，故选C
                	</p>
          	</answer>
		</exercise>


        <!-- Q8 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    设<m>f(x,y)=\left\{ \begin{matrix}
                        \frac{xy}{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}},  &amp;  {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}\ne 0,  \\
                        0,  &amp;  {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}=0,  \\
                     \end{matrix} \right.</m> . 求<m>f_{x}^{\prime }(x,y)</m>，<m>f_{y}^{\prime }(x,y).</m> 
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解：当<m>{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}\ne 0</m>时</p>
                    <p>
                        <me>\begin{array}{*{35}{l}}
                           f_{x}^{\prime }(x,y)=\frac{y\left( {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}} \right)-xy\cdot 2x}{{{\left( {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}} \right)}^{2}}}=\frac{{{y}^{3}}-{{x}^{2}}y}{{{\left( {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}} \right)}^{2}}}  \\
                           f_{y}^{\prime }(x,y)=\frac{x\left( {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}} \right)-xy\cdot 2y}{{{\left( {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}} \right)}^{2}}}=\frac{{{x}^{3}}-x{{y}^{2}}}{{{\left( {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}} \right)}^{2}}}  \\
                        \end{array}</me>
                        </p><p>当 <m>{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}=0</m>时，</p><p>
                        <me>\begin{aligned}
                           f_{x}^{\prime }(0,0) &amp; =\underset{x\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{f(x,0)-f(0,0)}{x-0}\\
                            &amp; =\underset{x\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{0-0}{x}\\
                            &amp; =0  \\
                           f_{y}^{\prime }(0,0) &amp; =\underset{y\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{f(0,y)-f(0,0)}{y-0}\\
                            &amp; =\underset{y\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{0-0}{y}\\
                            &amp; =0  \\
                        \end{aligned}</me>
                        
                        </p><p>所以</p><p>
                        <me>\begin{array}{*{35}{l}}
                           f_{x}^{\prime }(x,y)=\left\{ \begin{matrix}
                           \frac{{{y}^{3}}-{{x}^{2}}y}{{{\left( {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}} \right)}^{2}}},  &amp;  {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}\ne 0,  \\
                           0,  &amp;  {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}=0;  \\
                        \end{matrix} \right.  \\
                           f_{y}^{\prime }(x,y)=\left\{ \begin{matrix}
                           \frac{{{x}^{3}}-x{{y}^{2}}}{{{\left( {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}} \right)}^{2}}},  &amp;  {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}\ne 0,  \\
                           0,  &amp;  {{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}=0.  \\
                        \end{matrix} \right.  \\
                        \end{array}</me>
                        
                        </p>
                        <p>注：此函数在点<m>(0,0)</m>不连续，但偏导数存在.
                    </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

        <!-- Q9 -->
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    讨论 <m>z=f(x,y)=\sqrt{{{x}^{2}}+{{y}^{2}}}</m>在<m>(0,0)</m>点的否连续, 及在<m>(0,0)</m>处偏导数是否存在.
                </p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    解：<m>\because \underset{\begin{matrix}
                        x\to 0  \\
                        y\to 0  \\
                     \end{matrix}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,f(x,y)=f(0,0)=0</m></p><p>
                     
                     <m>\therefore f(x,y)</m>在<m>(0,0)</m>点连续</p><p>
                     
                     <me>\begin{aligned}
                     \because \underset{x\to {{0}^{-}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{f(x,0)-f(0,0)}{x-0} &amp; =\underset{x\to {{0}^{-}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{\sqrt{{{x}^{2}}}}{x}\\
                      &amp; =\underset{x\to {{0}^{-}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{-x}{x}\\
                      &amp; =-1
                     \end{aligned}</me>
                     
                     </p><p>而
                     
                     <me>\begin{aligned}
                     \underset{x\to {{0}^{+}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{f(x,0)-f(0,0)}{x-0} &amp; =\underset{x\to {{0}^{+}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{\sqrt{{{x}^{2}}}}{x}\\
                      &amp; =\underset{x\to {{0}^{-}}}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{x}{x}\\
                      &amp; =1
                     \end{aligned}</me>
                     
                     </p><p><m>\therefore \underset{x\to 0}{\mathop{\lim }}\,\frac{f(x,0)-f(0,0)}{x-0}</m>不存在
                     
                     </p><p>由对称性可知 <m>\lim\limits_{y\to 0}\frac{f(0,y)-f(0,0)}{y-0}</m>不存在
                     
                     </p><p>即<m>f(x,y)</m>在<m>(0,0)</m>处的两个偏导数不存在
                </p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>

